-- KKR bids up to $1.73 billion for Australia's Perpetual
-- 
-- Sun Oct 17, 2010 6:54pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/10/17/us-perpetual-kkr-idUSTRE69G1SE20101017

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Private equity firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co ( KKR.N ) has bid A$38 to A$40 a share for Australia's Perpetual ( PPT.AX ), valuing the fund manager at up to $1.73 billion, a 29 percent premium to Friday's close. 

 Perpetual, which has retained Goldman Sachs ( GS.N ) as its adviser, said it was considering the indicative, non-binding proposal and asked shareholders to take no action immediately. (Reporting by  Narayanan Somasundaram ; Editing by  Mark Bendeich )